column1: As a developer, I need an API to allow my applications (e.g. Mendix) to publish address changes to CCR.
column29:
An API is needed to allow external (outside of iPaaS) applications to publish address changes in the CCR database. The API needs to be secure and published internally.Â 

Â 

This doc explains why this is valuable:Â [http://wave.brighton-hove.gov.uk/LGCSDocumentLibrary/Health%20and%20safety/CCR/Updating%20a%20CCR%20Address%2013.03.17.docx]

Â 

*Updating a Client of Concern Address*

{color:#d04437}The nature of the Achieve system means that the only way to show a change of address for a perpetrator on the Clients of Concern Register (CCR) is to raise a new incident form{color}.Â  This process is being reviewed by ICT but in the interim staff will need to record details as a new Violence & Aggression incident as follows:
 * *Part A* (incident details) type in words to the effect that Mr/Mrs ** is known to have moved from **** to ****. Whatever is typed here shows on CCR.
 * *Perpetrator details* â€“ select the perpetrator name from the drop down list and over-type the address fields as relevant.
 * *Manager Review* section â€“ type in â€˜Address change onlyâ€™ into each box. This does not show on CCR and so can be kept brief.
 * *Manager Review* â€“ the questionnaire still needs to be completed as known
 * *Gatekeeper Review* - can just agree with manager and tick â€˜update CCRâ€™.
 * *Letter task* â€“ Manager can select no letter being sent.
 * *The Health & Safety Team* â€“ can take action to exclude the report from statistics.

These steps represent a lengthy workaround that could be solved with a much simpler feature.

 * Scheduled - is it scheduled and how often.
 * Accurate - Does data reflect reality
